    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\n1. Run the code and observe.\r\n2. *Discuss: The `Painter` passed over a paint bucket. What do you think its purpose is?*\r\n3. Uncomment (delete the `#`'s) the code on lines 11-14, 18, 20, and 22. Then run the program. \r\n4. *Discuss:* \r\n\t- *Was your prediction about the bucket accurate?*\r\n    - *What does the number on the bucket represent?*\r\n5. Paint a yellow line to the cone.\r\n\t- See the [documentation](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1x3xmKI_ADq8GaGoI0XGX9pJIE4VmPM3iXq_qIHeo7r4/edit?usp=sharing) for how to change the color of the paint. \r\n\r\n---\r\n###AI Tutor Support\r\n\r\n::: details [**Not sure what the bucket does?**]\r\nAsk AI: \r\n- What does `take_paint()` do in the Neighborhood?\r\n- What happens if I call `paint()` without calling `take_paint()` first?\r\n:::\r\n\r\n::: details [**Stuck on painting?**]\r\nAsk AI:\r\n- How do I change the color of the paint?\r\n- How do I paint a straight line?\r\n:::\r\n",
    "start_sources": {
      "files": {
        "0": {
          "id": "0",
          "name": "main.py",
          "language": "py",
          "contents": "from neighborhood import Painter\n\nzoe = Painter()\n\nzoe.move()\nzoe.move()\nzoe.move()\nzoe.turn_left()\nzoe.turn_left()\nzoe.turn_left()\nzoe.move()\n\n#zoe.take_paint()\n#zoe.take_paint()\n#zoe.take_paint()\n\nzoe.move()\n#zoe.paint(\"white\")\nzoe.move()\n#zoe.paint(\"white\")\nzoe.move()\n#zoe.paint(\"white\")",
          "folderId": "0",
